race.comment: MILE A MINUTE (7) has a strong record this track and trip with 15 wins and seven placings from 23 starts. Below best last time at Bendigo (24.09) in a Special conditions G2, finishing a 6 length sixth. Looks a leading chance on best. CATCH SOME RAYS (4) flew the lids with a fast early split and went on to clock 19.16 when a 1.2 lengths winner over 350m at this track. One of the prime contenders. AFTER THE SIREN (2) was out of the money at this circuit last start but can make amends. Something for the Multiples: FURIOSO RICK (5)
